headline: Big Bank earnings, CPI data, Fed commentary: What to Watch
summary: Here's what investors are watching on Tuesday, July 15. Big Banks will be kicking off earnings season in earnest, with JPMorgan (JPM), Wells Fargo (WFC), Citigroup (C), and Bank of New York Mellon (BK) releasing results. The Bureau of Labor Statistics will release June's Consumer Price Index (CPI) data, giving investors a fresh look at the US economy. Federal Reserve officials, including Fed governor Michelle Bowman, Fed governor Michael Barr, Boston Fed president Susan Collins, and Dallas Fed president Lorie Logan, will comment on the state of the US economy. headline: Stock Market Rally Faces Key Summer Stretch. Its Fate Is in Trump’s Hands.
summary: Investors are heading into a crucial three-week stretch amid a surge in uncertainty tied to key elements of President Donald Trump’s economic strategy.  Looking into the back half of the year, Wall Street analysts remain cautious, with the median year-end forecast of 14 banks and investment firms holding at around 6279, according to data compiled by freelance journalist and chartered financial analyst Mike Zaccardi.  Tariff risks, meanwhile, have accelerated sharply, with the president unveiling new levies of 30% on goods from the European Union and Mexico over the weekend.
